snippet.textDisplay: 6 gigabit/sec... Most 4G barely hits 20 mbit, we're nowhere near the bandwidth limit for 4G in 99% of the world. HSPA+ is barely slower than 4G in most places. The vast majority of people still have like 10-20 mbit connections at home that interrupt, glitch and bottleneck all the time, yet people are talking about gigabit home internet and 5 gigabit mobile broadband. What good is it when your plan only lets you download 2 GB in a month. These people need a reality check. Focus on improving the quality of people's internet vs. increasing theoretical limits that no one will reach in the near future.
